-- Chile and Hong Kong Sign Free Trade Agreement
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-09-07T11:50:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-07/chile-and-hong-kong-sign-free-trade-agreement.html
Chile  and Hong Kong signed a free
trade agreement today as part of the ceremonies of the 20th
Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation summit in Vladivostok, Russia.  Trade between Chile and Hong Kong reached $500 million last
year and should double in the near future, Chilean President
Sebastian Pinera was cited as saying in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Philip Sanders at 
 psanders@bloomberg.net . 